S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
S E N A T E R E S O L U T I O N
EXTENDING THE REPORTING DATE OF THE SPECIAL LEGISLATIVE COMMISSION
TO STUDY THE GOVERNANCE STRUCTURE OF RHODE ISLAND'S PUBLIC
EDUCATION SYSTEM
Introduced By: Senator Louis P. DiPalma
Date Introduced: March 27, 2025
Referred To: Placed on the Senate Consent Calendar
1 RESOLVED, That the special legislative commission created by resolution No. 364
2 passed by the Senate at its January session, A.D. 2024, and approved June 11, 2024, entitled
3 "Senate Resolution Creating a Special Legislative Commission to Study the Governance
4 Structure of Rhode Island’s Public Education System” is hereby authorized to continue its study
5 and make a report to the Senate on or before April 1, 2026, and said commission shall expire on
6 June 1, 2026; and be it further
7 RESOLVED, That the time for reporting authorized by resolution No. 364, passed by the
8 General Assembly at its January session, A.D. 2024, and approved June 11, 2024, be and the
9 same is hereby rescinded.
